                  <additions><list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#2v">f. 2v</locus>
                           <desc>: Note concerning events in the lives (?) of Evangelists (Matthew,
                              Mark, Luke and John).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Hardly readable. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#98rb">ff. 98rb-99</locus>
                           <desc>ra: Text concerning the value of common Orthodox prayers.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> In Amharic. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#99ra">f. 99ra</locus>
                           <desc>: Note concerning dates of celebrating some feasts, with a small,
                              crude calendaric table.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in Gǝʿǝz and Amharic. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#99va">f. 99va</locus>
                           <desc>: Unidentified text.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> In Amharic. Recent and hardly readable, written in pink. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus target="#99vb">f. 99vb</locus>
                           <desc>: ʾAsmat-prayer. </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> The title (?) is written in the upper margin: “And you who have
                              terrified the idols...”. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a6">
                           <locus target="#100v">f. 100v</locus>
                           <desc>: Protective prayer to God, a recipe for a certain medicine, and a
                              short protective prayer mentioning St Mary.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in Gǝʿǝz and Amharic. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- A chain of black dots and a red line, probably
                           separating the text passages (?), on fols.: 21v, 23r, 41r, 41v, 42v, 49r,
                           50r, 53r, 61v, 62v, 63r, 64v, 67r, 71r, 72r, 73r, 77v, 87r, 93v.&#xD; -
